gan’s life. Organized chronologically, they give an impression of his development as a writer, his ever-strengthening religious commitment, and his role as teacher. As a sampling of pieces from the late 1920s to the early 1980s, Shorter Papers testifies to the cumulative impact of Lonergan’s work, as well as to the amazing continuity that he maintained throughout his career as an author and intellectual.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aTheologyy20th century. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aCroken, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoran, Robert M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoran, S.J., Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMonsour, H. Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268479940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442684799423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442684799.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK